reviews.headline: Love love love
reviews.comments: I have a terrible time finding a nude lip shade, and hydra honey is IT. MLBB to a T.  Super glossy finish and great color, I love it so much.

reviews.headline: Perfect for all skin color and everyday wear
reviews.comments: I made sure to do my research to pick either Bubblegum Burst or Dripping in Rose. Thankfully one was out of stock and felt like it was picked out for me. Natural look and pink just the right shade for everyday. Then later I got Bubblegum burst to try.

reviews.headline: Love this product
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. This has become my new favorite lipgloss. The color is vibrant, the scent is very natural. Smooth creamy texture makes it easy to apply. Will be purchasing more in the future. Would definitely recommend to friends and family

reviews.headline: Colors are too bright
reviews.comments: The colors online dont match what they look like in person at all. They're incredibly bright and rich. I'm not a huge fan of bright colors since they don't look good on me and they tend to be a mess. I like trying out new stains because I hate having to reapply lip products but I'll stick to the Fenty ones I've been enjoying for now.

reviews.headline: love this serum!
reviews.comments: I love the color this lea es my lips after the gloss wears off. Keeps my lips moisturized and natural looking.

reviews.headline: These are going to be my staple for my fall lip combos
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] These really surprised me! I thought I would absolutely need a liner with these but I honestly feel like you can get away without one! They're perfect shades for a fall transition lip combo and I'll def be playing around with these more

reviews.headline: I love the look and the feel, but I hate having to reapply.
reviews.comments: The color is perfect. The texture is silky going on and dries comfortably. The price is affordable and easily justified! It is small and fits easily in my pocket! BUT...after an hour-long meeting where I talk a lot or drink, I have to reapply, which is why I'm giving it four stars. :(

reviews.headline: Â¡IT LOOKED GOOD ON THEM!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I'm always down to try new products, even tho I'm not that in to glossy/sticky formulas. The colors were nice and did last long. Ended up gifting them to my family who are into gloss and they really enjoyed wearing it. Â¡It looked great on them! That's why I give it a good review, it's a good product but the glossy consistency is not for me.

reviews.headline: Actually leaves a stain
reviews.comments: Idk why they chose to promote with such unflattering pictures this leaves a very cute stain super similar to the color it goes on as and it's available in such cute colors too! the second i thought i lost mine i bought 4 more. bestwhen bought on sale

reviews.headline: long lasting and gorgeous
reviews.comments: I wore this for the first time on a 90+ degree day where I was sweating buckets outside...the stain lasted throughout the entire day and the shine in the beginning was fairly long lasting as well! the shades are gorgeous and my lips felt cushioned and hydrated on application. I'll definitely get more colors.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments:
I love this product. It stays on really well. The trick is blotting it. When you first apply it can be a bit goopy. Blotting will help with this and help set it. 
Colors are fantastic. So far my favorite is bubblegum burst.

reviews.headline: Set it and forget it!
reviews.comments: Game changer alert!  A lip product that lasts all day without touch-ups?  Yes, please!

reviews.headline: ðŸ’‹Apply it once and done!!
reviews.comments: Finally a lip product I can put on once and it's here to stay!  No more worrying after I put it on before I go to the office in the morning, and then later checking to make sure it's still on when I'm out with friends at night.  Set it and forget it!

reviews.headline: Misleading
reviews.comments: I ordered the shade "drippin in rose", which in all product images appeared to be a color much darker than what I received - IRL it is a light pink. The product itself is smears easily and does not leave much color on the lips. NYX lip products are usually good but this one isn't it.

reviews.headline: I'm mad I waited so long to try this!
reviews.comments: It feels sooooooo good. OH MY GOD. So plush and hydrating. Even without the stain factor, it's truly a beautiful gloss. The stain is just a bonus! It wears and fades so beautifully. I'm obsessed! The only negative is that the colors do not 100% match the photos, so it's best to swatch in-store if possible.  Also, a lot of the shades stain the same (a red/burgundy color), so even though the glosses are different colors upon application, you don't need multiples of this because the end result is similar. Drippin' in Rose is a GORGEOUS rose/mauvey nude for med-deep skin tones, perfect for everyday wear. I'm a Fenty 420, so if we're shade twins, you need to pick up that shade IMMEDIATELY.

reviews.headline: Nyx lip
reviews.comments: I love love love nyx. Havent tried a product i dont like. Already repurchased this too. Lasts a long time. Non drying. Very pretty.

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Absolutely love The hydrating aspect is no joke not to mention it lasted forever No texture just smooth I already purchased one on my own because they are that good plus you cant compete with the price

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again and again
reviews.comments: This product makes my life easier I put it on when I start my routine and wipe it off when I finish it lasts the whole day.

reviews.headline: No Corals or Peach tones
reviews.comments: Nothing is more disappointing than a limited shade range in nude colors. Nude may be kn style but does not work for everyone. They can really wash out certain skin tones. Bring in the warm brighter colors and stop already with just nude shades.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Lip IV Hydrating Gloss Stain in a dark reddish-purple shade is a stunning lip product that strikes a perfect balance between hydration, color payoff, and lasting power. I was gifted this lipgloss in exchange for a I was gifted this lipgloss in exchange for an honest review, and I can honestly honestly say it's amazing!!!The formula feels lightweight yet nourishing, providing a smooth, non-sticky finish that leaves your lips feeling soft and moisturized throughout the day. The dark reddish-purple shade is rich and bold, offering a sophisticated, slightly edgy look that's perfect for both day and night wear.

What sets this product apart is its ability to act as both a gloss and a stain. The gloss gives an instant, high-shine finish that catches the light beautifully, while the stain subtly sets into the lips, leaving behind a natural, long-lasting tint even as the gloss wears off. This makes it an ideal option for those who want the best of both worldsâ€”glossy allure with the longevity of a stain.

The color itself is versatile, with just the right balance of depth and vibrancy, making it flattering on a wide range of skin tones. It's bold enough to make a statement but not overpowering, offering a sophisticated pop of color that feels effortlessly chic. Whether you're going for a bold evening look or a more understated daytime vibe, this lip gloss stain delivers the perfect amount of drama and moisture in one sleek package.

Overall, if you're looking for a lip product that combines hydration, a gorgeous pop of dark color, and lasting power, the Lip IV Hydrating Gloss Stain in this deep reddish-purple shade is a winner.
faceoff_positive.headline: Formula is amazing

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review. This gloss is super pigmented. It definitely has a creamy serum like texture. It is not sticky or gooey. You get a ton of color with just one swipe and it smells a little bit like coconut. I put it over my dry lips with nothing else and I can say that it definitely left them very hydrated after I wiped away the gloss. so this would be a pretty cool product, if you're going out, put your gloss on and then through the night it It kind of came off because you still have a slight stain afterwards, which is pretty cool. I'd like the idea. The stain afterwards doesn't look the best, but you could always touch it up with maybe even like a clear gloss once it wipes away or Chapstick or just reapply it. I like the packaging. It's a cute little component, doe foot applicator. I wish that they had these in lighter colors, but I did really like this color specifically, and I don't normally like red gloss or red lipstick so overall pretty nice product!
faceoff_negative.headline: Very hydrating, super pigmented!
